  "abstract": "Sorghum and Millet are the first and second most important cereal crops, respectively, of the Sudan. Most of the sorghum is grown in the central rainlands where the seasonal precipatationis unpredictable; where as the bulk of the pearl millet in the country is grown in western Sudan where the rainfall is even less reliable....",
